statuses.text: I don't believe in fashion victims. I believe in fashion villains.
Why follow trends when you can follow the shadows?
My wardrobe consists of various shades of black, with occasional accents of despair
Why wear your heart on your sleeve when you can wear it on a pentagram?
I find beauty in the macabre, and my closet reflects that aesthetic.
Clothes may maketh the man, but they definitely maketh the monster.
Black is not just a color, it's a lifestyle.
Life is short, and so are my skirts. But my disdain for pastels is everlasting.
My fashion philosophy? The darker, the better.
Why settle for silver linings when you can embrace the beauty of storm clouds?
I prefer my accessories haunted and my outfits haunted-er.
If you can't see the beauty in skulls, you're not looking hard enough.
My style icon? Morticia Addams, obviously. She taught me that elegance is eternal, especially in black velvet.
My ideal date night outfit? A little black dress and a lot of dark humor.
Why wear flowers in your hair when you can wear thorns?
I've mastered the art of making 'mourning' a year-round trend.
Fashion tip: Add a touch of cobweb to any ensemble for that instant gothic glam.
